dataLineage.statement:
Original administrative boundary dataset were acquired from 1:25,000 topographic map (Peta Bumi series) made by Bakosurtanal, Indonesia. These data were modified for the adoption to the coastline data from 1:50,000 topographic map made by Defence Imagery and Geospatial Organisation (DIGO), Australia.
Districts, Sub-districts and Sucos are promulgated in Diploma Ministerial No. 9/2004 by the Ministry of State Administration. Because one administrative unit may be composed of more than two singlepart polygons, .the number of sub-districts (65) is different from that of polygons (69).
